15/08/2007
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Veteran Czech diplomat Ivan Busniak has been appointed as the new head of the Office of the High Representative (OHR) in Banja Luka. 
He will succeed Orlando Fusco on September 1st. 
High Representative and EU Special Representative in BiH Miroslav Lajcak tapped Busniak for the post.
Separately Tuesday (August 14th), the OHR confirmed that Lajcak is holding talks on police reform with leaders of various political parties. 
Lajcak has set an end- of- September deadline for an agreement on police reform, which is key to signing a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU. 
(OHR website, FENA - 14/08/07)
